verbose_text: We believe that the stronger effects of TWEAK compared to TNF-alpha on MyHC degradation in cultured myotubes [XREF_BIBR], is attributed, at least in parts, to the TWEAK 's ability to cause sustained activation of NF-kappaB, which stimulates the activity of UPS through augmenting the expression of MuRF1 and other components of proteasome [XREF_BIBR, XREF_BIBR].
